# From https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/skos/skos-rules.n3
#
# BLOCKED: beyond the ordinary forward-chaining SKOS rules (subject/inverse
# properties, transitivity -- all of which this engine's plain rule support
# already handles), skos-rules.n3 also contains genuine consistency-check
# rules with a bodyless `=> false.` head (e.g. "Hierarchical and associative
# relations are disjoint": `{?x skos:related ?y. ?x skos:broaderTransitive
# ?y} => false.`), predicate-object-list-with-shared-subject syntax
# (`?c skos:prefLabel ?l; skos:altLabel ?l`), and rules requiring
# `func:lang-from-PlainLiteral` (the `func:` RIF-builtin-function namespace,
# entirely unimplemented here). `=> false` isn't a valid Triple this engine's
# `Rule.head: Triple` can represent at all (there's no boolean/denial rule
# head type), so parsing/loading the ruleset outright would need engine
# changes beyond this ticket's builtins-and-conformance scope. Not vendored
# as runnable input.
